{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos142.erdos_142 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos142.erdos_142.","id":"vf_1d1f4138c05272ae","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #142: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $r_k(N)$ be the largest possible size of a subset of $\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ that does not contain any non-trivial $k$-term arithmetic progression. Prove an asymptotic formula for $r_k(N)$. Current best: The best known upper bounds for $r_k(N)$ are due to Kelley and Meka \\cite{KeMe23} for $k=3$, Green and Tao \\cite{GrTa17} for $k=4$, and Leng, Sah, and Sawhney \\cite{LSS24} for $k\\geq 5$. An asymptotic formula is still far out of reach, even for $k=3$. Prize: $10000. OEIS: A003002, A003003, A003004, A003005. Tags: additive combinatorics, arithmetic progressions.","id":"vf_d508f2cbffbd5a92","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/142.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_1d1f4138c05272ae","source_root":"sha256:a4d62c3b7a2ca0a02a1bf4ce1b4ad0ffb06b6f2f61ff9f5b58ed8ee07d8b2bf1","target":"erdos:142","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_1d1f4138c05272ae","source_root":"sha256:a4d62c3b7a2ca0a02a1bf4ce1b4ad0ffb06b6f2f61ff9f5b58ed8ee07d8b2bf1","target":"vf_d508f2cbffbd5a92","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_d508f2cbffbd5a92","source_root":"sha256:a4d62c3b7a2ca0a02a1bf4ce1b4ad0ffb06b6f2f61ff9f5b58ed8ee07d8b2bf1","target":"erdos:142","trust":"signed"